            <div class="section-text">
                <h2>Every Narrative Tells a Life</h2>
                <p>I developed my writing skills starting when I was 11 years old – I’d watch fantasy and adventure movies nonstop, getting lost in every magical world and epic quest on screen. One day I thought, ‘What if I made my own stories too?’ So I began writing down horror, fantasy, and all sorts of tales in notebooks, even filling up whole pads with my ideas, scribbling whenever inspiration hit me, whether I was in class or at home! </p><br><br><br>
                
                
                <p>I’d even let my friends and classmates read the stories in my notebooks to ask if they liked them, their feedback helped me figure out what worked and what I could make better.
             From creating made-up worlds with their own rules and histories to dreaming up weird creatures that lived in hidden forests or dark caves, I built my style one page at a time. Over the years, I kept honing my craft, learning how to make characters feel real and plots that keep readers hooked and that’s how writing became such a big part of who I am now. </p>
            </div>
